8/7/86  forum_request:  remove_meeting, rm

Syntax: rm {meeting_names} {-control_args}


Function:  removes meetings to the user's "forum" search list by deleting
links to them from the directory >udd>Project>Person>meetings.


Arguments:
meeting_names
   are names of forum meetings to be removed from the search list.  The star
   convention is allowed.


Control arguments:
-brief, -bf
   suppresses some informational messages.
-check, -ck
   lists all links to meeting in >udd>Project>Person>meetings that point
   to non-existent meetings.  Incompatible with -cleanup.
-cleanup
   removes all links to forum meetings from >udd>Project>Person>meetings
   that point to non-existent meetings. Incompatible with -check.
-current_meeting, -cmtg
   removes the current meeting from the search list.


-directory PATH, -dr PATH
   removes the links from the specified directory instead of the default
   directory of >udd>Project>Person>meetings.
-long, -lg
   prints all informational messages.  (Default)


Notes:  If a meeting is found through some other entry in the "forum"
search list, the site's central forum directory for instance, this command
can not remove it.
